The paper deals with fundamental problems in combinatorial optimization, specifically bin packing and makespan scheduling, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), machine learning (cs.LG), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of streaming algorithms to solve these problems suggests a focus on space-efficient algorithms, which is a common theme in the aforementioned sub-categories.
